estic violence that has demonstrated exemplary service to those affected through an alliance with a local sexual or domestic violence service agency  Grace is a board member at Project Horizon  a nonprofit organization whose purpose is to prevent dating  domestic  and sexual violence in the Rockbridge area  In addition to his work on behalf of Project Horizon  Grace serves on the Governor s Task Force on Combating Campus Sexual Violence  a group that was convened by Gov  Terry McAuliffe in 2014 to address sexual violence on college and university campuses around the commonwealth  Taking over the inspector general and Title IX coordinator s post is Col  Jeffrey Boobar  86  Boobar  who majored in history and modern languages and cultures at VMI  served in the U S  Army s 2nd Armored Cavalry Regiment for four years before embarking on a 23 year career with the U S  Drug Enforcement Administration  It was during Boobar s time with the Drug Enforcement Administration that the foundation for his return to VMI was laid  In 1993  Boobar s wife  Audrey  needed a bone marrow transplant to treat invasive breast cancer  and at the time the health insurance provided to federal employees didn t cover the six figure cost of that treatment  Cadets taking up a freewill offering in barracks collected more than  5 000  Boobar recalled  a sum that he termed  unbelievable  In 1994  Boobar came to VMI and addressed the Corps of Cadets to thank them  At the time  he said  he told himself that if he ever had an opportunity to give back to the Institute  he would take advantage of it   VMI literally saved my wife s life   a debt that can never be repaid  said Boobar  adding that his wife has now been free of cancer for 22 years   I wanted to come back and give service to the Institute  Boobar participated in Georgetown University s Government Affairs Institute Congressional Fellowship program and twice received both the U S  Army Commendation Medal and the International Narcotics Enforcement Officers Association Special Award of Honor  He comes to VMI from JP Morgan Chase   Co  where since his retirement from DEA last year he has served as vice president and compliance manager for global financial crimes compliance   VMI  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Retiring VMI Title IX Coordinator Honored  skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural Sciences ROTC Enrichment Institute Honors Program International Programs Service Opportunities Summer Programs Institute Writing Program Research Support Cadet Counseling Career Services Disabilities Services Miller Academic Center Advising Math Resource Center The Writing Center Resources Registrar Financial Aid Canvas Login Dean s Office Career Services Bookstore Cadet Computing Admissions Corps Life Athletics Library   Archives Preston Library Library Home Find Books Departments Media Equipment Technical Services Visitor Information Archives Archives Home Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Give Close Menu Communications   Marketing News and Features Construction News Institute Report Photos   Videos Cindy Bither Administrative Assistant P   540  464 7207 F   540  464 7443 111 Smith Hall Lexington  VA 24450 Retiring VMI Title IX Coordinator Honored Col  Bill Grace  left  and Col  Jeff Boobar  Retired DEA Agent  VMI Alumnus  Takes Up Position LEXINGTON  Va  June 25  2015   Col  Bill Grace  soon to retire as VMI s inspector general and Title IX coordinator  has been honored with the Uncommon Ally Award  given by the Virginia Sexual and Domestic Violence Action Alliance  The Uncommon Ally Award is presented to an individual  group  organization  or business not typically associated with the fight against sexual or domestic violence that has demonstrated exemplary service to those affected through an alliance with a local sexual or domestic violence service agency  Grace is a board member at Project Horizon  a nonprofit organization whose purpose is to prevent dating  domestic  and sexual violence in the Rockbridge area  In addition to his work on behalf of Project Horizon  Grace serves on the Governor s Task Force on Combating Campus Sexual Violence  a group that was convened by Gov  Terry McAuliffe in 2014 to address sexual violence on college and university campuses around the commonwealth  Taking over the inspector general and Title IX coordinator s post is Col  Jeffrey Boobar  86  Boobar  who majored in history and modern languages and cultures at VMI  served in the U S  Army s 2nd Armored Cavalry Regiment for four years before embarking on a 23 year career with the U S  Drug Enforcement Administration  It was during Boobar s time with the Drug Enforcement Administration that the foundation for his return to VMI was laid  In 1993  Boobar s wife  Audrey  needed a bone marrow transplant to treat invasive breast cancer  and at the time the health insurance provided to federal employees didn t cover the six figure cost of that treatment  Cadets taking up a freewill offering in barracks collected more than  5 000  Boobar recalled  a sum that he termed  unbelievable  In 1994  Boobar came to VMI and addressed the Corps of Cadets to thank them  At the time  he said  he told himself that if he ever had an opportunity to give back to the Institute  he would take advantage of it   VMI literally saved my wife s life   a debt that can never be repaid  said Boobar  adding that his wife has now been free of cancer for 22 years   I wanted to come back and give service to the Institute  Boobar participated in Georgetown University s Government Affairs Institute Congressional Fellowship program and twice received both the U S  Army Commendation Medal and the International Narcotics Enforcement Officers Association Special Award of Honor  He comes to VMI from JP Morgan Chase   Co  where since his retirement from DEA last year he has served as vice president and compliance manager for global financial crimes compliance   VMI  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Retiring VMI Title IX Coordinator Honored    Retiring VMI Title IX Coordinator Honored                skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New 