   540  464 7207 F   540  464 7443 111 Smith Hall Lexington  VA 24450 Retiring VMI Title IX Coordinator Honored Col  Bill Grace  left  and Col  Jeff Boobar  Retired DEA Agent  VMI Alumnus  Takes Up Position LEXINGTON  Va  June 25  2015   Col  Bill Grace  soon to retire as VMI s inspector general and Title IX coordinator  has been honored with the Uncommon Ally Award  given by the Virginia Sexual and Domestic Violence Action Alliance  The Uncommon Ally Award is presented to an individual  group  organization  or business not typically associated with the fight against sexual or domestic violence that has demonstrated exemplary service to those affected through an alliance with a local sexual or domestic violence service agency  Grace is a board member at Project Horizon  a nonprofit organization whose purpose is to prevent dating  domestic  and sexual violence in the Rockbridge area  In addition to his work on behalf of Project Horizon  Grace serves on the Governor s Task Force on Combating Campus Sexual Violence  a group that was convened by Gov  Terry McAuliffe in 2014 to address sexual violence on college and university campuses around the commonwealth  Taking over the inspector general and Title IX coordinator s post is Col  Jeffrey Boobar  86  Boobar  who majored in history and modern languages and cultures at VMI  served in the U S  Army s 2nd Armored Cavalry Regiment for four years before embarking on a 23 year career with the U S  Drug Enforcement Administration  It was during Boobar s time with the Drug Enforcement Administration that the foundation for his return to VMI was laid  In 1993  Boobar s wife  Audrey  needed a bone marrow transplant to treat invasive breast cancer  and at the time the health insurance provided to federal employees didn t cover the six figure cost of that treatment  Cadets taking up a freewill offering in barracks collected more than  5 000  Boobar recalled  a sum that he termed  unbelievable  In 1994  Boobar came to VMI and addressed the Corps of Cadets to thank them  At the time  he said  he told himself that if he ever had an opportunity to give back to the Institute  he would take advantage of it   VMI literally saved my wife s life   a debt that can never be repaid  said Boobar  adding that his wife has now been free of cancer for 22 years   I wanted to come back and give service to the Institute  Boobar participated in Georgetown University s Government Affairs Institute Congressional Fellowship program and twice received both the U S  Army Commendation Medal and the International Narcotics Enforcement Officers Association Special Award of Honor  He comes to VMI from JP Morgan Chase   Co  where since his retirement from DEA last year he has served as vice president and compliance manager for global financial crimes compliance   VMI Communications   Marketing News and Features Construction News Institute Report Photos   Videos Cindy Bither Administrative Assistant P   540  464 7207 F   540  464 7443 111 Smith Hall Lexington  VA 24450  Communications   Marketing News and Features Construction News Institute Report Photos   Videos Cindy Bither Administrative Assistant P   540  464 7207 F   540  464 7443 111 Smith Hall Lexington  VA 24450 Communications   Marketing News and Features Construction News Institute Report Photos   Videos Communications   Marketing Communications   Marketing News and Features News and Features Construction News Construction News Institute Report Institute Report Photos   Videos Photos   Videos        Cindy Bither Administrative Assistant P   540  464 7207 F   540  464 7443 111 Smith Hall Lexington  VA 24450 Cindy Bither Administrative Assistant P   540  464 7207 F   540  464 7443 111 Smith Hall Lexington  VA 24450 Cindy Bither       Retiring VMI Title IX Coordinator Honored Col  Bill Grace  left  and Col  Jeff Boobar  Retired DEA Agent  VMI Alumnus  Takes Up Position LEXINGTON  Va  June 25  2015   Col  Bill Grace  soon to retire as VMI s inspector general and Tit